FASTAPI SETUP :

create virtual environment  - python -m venv  environment_name

To activate -  environment_name/scripts/activate

create file - main.py

install -  pip install fastapi uvicorn

run - uvicon main:app --reload  ||  uvicorn app.main:app --reload (if we create folder inside venv)

Auto Documentation ( postman or thunderclient ) :  http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DATABASE CONNECTION : (postgresql password : post123)

install - pip install sqlalchemy psycopg2-binary python-dotenv

create .env file with data -  DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:post123@localhost:5432/fastapi_db

create database connection file -   database.py

create model (table creation) connection file -  model.py

create schema file for validating repsonse and request -   schemas.py

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


migration using -- alembic  

install -- pip install alembic

run (it will create new folder named 
    alembic inside the backend folder)    - alembic init alembic  

open (alembic.ini ) file -  search for  (sqlalchemy.url = ) 
                           replace your db connection credentials 


open (alembic folder inside env.py) -  add import (from app.database import Base
                                         from app import models)
                                                    
                                      search for (target_metadata)
                                      this (target_metadata = none) to  ( target_metadata = Base.metadata)


First migration (existing tables)  -  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "initial"

                                      alembic upgrade head


Before anything (important)
Make sure you REMOVED this from main.py:
Base.metadata.create_all(bind=engine)


General Rule (Remember forever)
1) Change models.py
2) Generate migration
3) Apply migration


alembic revision --autogenerate -m "message"
alembic upgrade head


